In [140]:
def values_corr (dataframe):
    th = 0.5
    cont = 0
    for fila in range(dataframe.shape[0]):
        for columna in range(dataframe.shape[1]):
            if np.abs(dataframe.iloc[fila, columna]) > th and  fila != columna:
                cont += 1
                print('{} : th = {} for variables {} and {}'.format(cont, round(dataframe.iloc[fila, columna],2), dataframe.columns[fila], dataframe.columns[columna]))

NEGOCIO relations and LINEA_DE_SERVICIO, it is because why the LINEA_DE_SERVICIO are the services provided to businesses (customers and their categorization). GENERACION and EDAD are closely related and GENERACION are slices of age periods. The NEGOCIO and the TIPO_DE_CONTRATO are related variables since the business (focus of types of services provided) change the type of contract used. INACTIVO and FONDEX is an unexpected variable and it is proposed to know their relationship (Insight). The NEGOCIO and the SECTOR have a relationship and it is explained that the business brings together target market niches (Sectors). If there is cause for the contract, it must be inactive because the relationship here is completely linear. ACTIVO and REGISTRO are related in that the first month of the collaborator, if he is withdrawn, this variable would also appear. It is true if the collaborator is withdrawn before the month. The service line and the sector have a close operational relationship, so this correlation coefficient between the two is clear, as with NEGOCIO, there is also a relationship between the level of risk and the sector, which is a very important finding.

Let us take a look at what we just got with the matrices above and make some analysis. First of all, let us keep in mind that we wait for an almost full linear relation between some kind of variables, for example, COD_CIUDAD_LABOR and CIUDAD_LABOR in 'data' database. Given that, we are not going to deal with that, but instead, let us focus on some interesting relations that matrices are telling us. Let us remember too that we have 3 databases into our project, but because the kind of these, we are only interested in 'data' and 'incapacidades' databases, and lastly their join. Besides, we got a number 'th' for every relation, where th > 0.5, and means the correlation between the two variables

Here are some important results indicating a warning on the linear relationships we are calculating. Before that, let us notice that COD_INCAPACIDAD and CLASE_NOMINA are so close linear related, and CLASE_NOMINA is telling us the type of employee, so, it has a large influence on the project's goal. On the other hand, CONCEPTO and NOMBRE IPS - ARL relationship is expected, although it does not look like that at a first sight. Finally, there is not any transitivity among the variables COD_DIAGNOSTICO, CONTINGENCIA and DIAS, taking COD_DIAGNOSTICO and CONTINGENCIA a lesser value than CONTINGENCIA and DIAS which is closer to the correlation value of DIAS and COD_DIAGNOSTICO. Before result shows us that we must be very careful with the analysis and understanding of the data.

First of all, it is important to point out that not all variables on the join were taken, the code approach we used did not allow such a task, so, a specific set of variables in the list data object named 'data4' is taken for the exercise. The variables election was based on what we considered relevant information according to the acquired expertise reached working on the project so as the meeting with technical team from EFICACIA.

Here we need to notice that a careful eye on the data must be kept, for example, notice that the variables ACTIVO and INACTIVO are linear dependent, however, the correlation values between ACTIVO and CAUSAL_FIN_CONTRATO, and INACTIVO and CAUSAL_FIN_CONTRATO are not the same, even there is around 20 percentual points away. Nevertheless, there is no sense between the ACTIVO and CAUSAL_FIN_CONTRATO relationship, because if the employee is working as the ACTIVO variable sugests, there is not any CAUSAL_FIN_CONTRATO variable applying.

Finally, in order to conclude, it is important to be very careful with the data (take a look at the linear dependent variables for example), to identify the kind of variables (and therefore apply the adequate kind of model), and to take the most relevant ones, suggesting graphs(scatter plots, for example, assured the kind of relation given for the matrix is right or not) and other kinds types of association measurements (going further than cramer and pearson).
